### Consequences
- Business logic remains isolated from external API implementation; if ViaCEP changes or is replaced, only the infrastructure adapter needs to change
- CQRS separates read and write responsibilities, improving clarity and scalability of use cases
- Layer separation improves readability, maintainability, and future testability
- The architecture is aligned with NestJS module conventions while preserving layered responsibilities
- The reduced scope is addressed without the overhead of implementing a full Hexagonal Architecture
- If the project grows and needs to consume multiple external APIs, new adapters can be added in infrastructure without impacting web/domain contracts
